This is an otherwise healthy man presents emergency room today with 1 week of exertional angina and dyspnea. Seen at and was reportedly found to have a troponin of 4.55 (could have been trop I?). Started on heparin and given aspirin at OS, then transferred for higher level of care. 
﻿
The pt is accompanied by his son and daughter, whom are both college students. He is currently in the visiting his children and is in for 17 more days.  The son provided translation. The pt started having substernal chest pain 1 week ago, only with walking.  He has never had the pain at rest.  He denies accompanying symptoms, including diaphoresis, nausea, arm/jaw pain.
